Adjust rack to middle position and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry
produce.

Dice @potatoes{12%oz} into ½-inch pieces. Peel @garlic{3%cloves}. Trim
@green beans{6%oz} if necessary. Trim and cut @scallions{4} into ½-inch
pieces. Zest and quarter @lemon{1}. Peel and mince or grate
@ginger{1%thumb}.

Place potatoes and whole garlic cloves in a #medium pot{} with enough salted
water to cover by 2 inches. Bring to a boil and cook until tender,
~{15-20%minutes}.

Reserve ½ cup potato cooking liquid, then drain. Return potatoes and garlic
to pot; keep covered off heat until ready to use in Step 5.

Pat @beef tenderloin filets{10%oz} dry with #paper towels{} and season
generously all over with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tbsp} in a #large pan{} over medium-high
heat. Add beef; sear on all sides until browned, ~{3-5%minutes}.

Turn off heat; transfer beef to a #baking sheet{}. Wipe out pan. Roast on
middle rack to desired doneness, ~{10-12%minutes}. Transfer beef to a
#cutting board{} to rest.

While beef roasts, heat a drizzle of oil in pan used for beef over high
heat. Add green beans and scallions; cook, stirring occasionally, until
charred and tender, ~{6-8%minutes}.

Turn off heat. Stir in lemon zest and @sesame seeds{1%tbsp}; season
generously with salt and pepper. Transfer to a #plate{}; wipe out pan.

While veggies cook, return pot with potatoes and garlic to stovetop
over medium heat. Add @cream sauce base{4%oz}, @horseradish paste{2%tsp},
and @cream cheese{2%tbsp}. Mash with a #potato masher{} until smooth and
creamy, adding splashes of reserved potato cooking liquid as needed. Cook
until warmed through, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Turn off heat and stir in @butter{1%tbsp} until melted; taste and season
with salt and pepper.

> Use 2 TBSP butter for 4 servings.

Heat a drizzle of oil in pan used for green beans over medium-high heat.
Add ginger and cook, stirring occasionally, until fragrant, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir in @sweet soy glaze{4%tbsp}, juice from half a lemon, and ¼ cup water.
Cook, stirring occasionally, until thickened and thoroughly combined,
~{1-3%minutes}.

Turn off heat and stir in @butter{1%tbsp}.

> Use 2 TBSP butter for 4 servings.

Slice beef against the grain.

Divide beef, green beans and scallions, and mashed potatoes between plates.
Drizzle beef with as much sauce as you like. Serve with remaining lemon
wedges on the side.

> Beef is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.